Backport of upstream fix for GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8 (langsmith arbitrary
server-side file read via attachment-validation guard bypass).

Replaces the three copy-pasted, identically-broken
isinstance(tuple)+isinstance(Path) checks in create_run, update_run, and
multipart_ingest with a single fail-closed helper that keys off the data
type (inline bytes vs. anything else). The old guard never fired for
JSON-deserialised shapes (list with str path), so arbitrary file paths
were opened.

Adapted from upstream commit 9c5515620f9bfa2145fc65d6f4353c4c8a3e96b6
(client.py hunks only; upstream test changes omitted -- tests are not
shipped at runtime and the 0.4.48 test layout differs).

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk
Target: langsmith==0.4.48 (PyPI sdist)

